value.value: A tuber axillary vegetative bud that is part of an aerial tuber.
A tuber axillary vegetative bud that is part of a subterranean tuber.

definition.value: A structure on the tuber surface that can sprout. In potatoes, axillary vegetative buds (eyes) can determine processing quality. Scale that the breeders use to rate the buds/sprouts of tubers: 1. none, 2. swollen eye, 3. sprout ca. 1/4 inch, 4. sprout ca. 1/2 inch, 5. sprout ca. 1 inch, 6. sprout ca. 2 inch, 7. sprout ca. 3 inch, 8. new top growth, 9. chain tubers.

value.value: A portion of shoot axis periderm (PO:0005048) that is part of a shoot axis tuber (PO:0004543).
A portion of tuber periderm that is part of an aerial tuber.
A portion of tuber periderm that is part of a subterranean tuber.

definition.value: The skin of young potatoes is epidermis while the skin of mature potatoes is periderm.

value.value: A portion of shoot axis epidermis (PO:0000112) that is part of a shoot axis tuber (PO:0004543).
A portion of shoot axis tuber epidermis (PO:0025046) that is part of an aerial tuber (PO:0004548).
A shoot axis tuber epidermis (PO:0025046) that is part of a subterranean shoot axis tuber (PO:0004547).

definition.value: The skin of young potatoes is epidermis while the skin of mature potatoes is periderm.

value.value: A tuber interfascicular region that is part of a subterranean tuber storage parenchyma.

definition.value: Because subterranean interfascicular regions in potato tubers form before the subterranean tuber perimedullary zone expands (PO:0025063), in mature potato tubers, the subterranean tuber interfascicular regions persist as rays that extend from the central pith to the eyes or subterranean tuber axillary vegetative buds (PO:0025042).

value.value: An interfascicular region that is part of a tuber storage parenchyma.
A tuber interfascicular region that is part of an aerial tuber storage parenchyma.
A portion of pith (PO:0006109) that is part of a tuber storage parenchyma (PO:0025036).
A portion of tuber pith (PO:0025052) that is part of a subterranean tuber storage parenchyma (PO:0025038).

definition.value: In potatoes, this is part of the flesh.

value.value: A portion of tuber pith (PO:0025052) that is part of an aerial tuber storage parenchyma (PO:0025039).
A portion of cortex (PO:0005708) that is part of a tuber storage parenchyma (PO:0025036).
A portion of tuber cortex that is part of an aerial tuber storage parenchyma.
A portion of tuber cortex that is part of a subterranean tuber storage parenchyma.
A portion of parenchyma (PO:0005421) that is the outer layer of the pith (PO:0006109).

definition.value: The term perimedullary zone is only used when the outer layer of the pith is distinct from the inner layer.

value.value: Any portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) other than epidermis (PO:0005679) or vascular tissue (PO:0009015).

definition.value: Develops from the ground meristem (PO:0025594).

value.value: A cardinal part of multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025498) that is thin and flat.

definition.value: PATO:0000407 (flat) and PATO:0000592 (thin).

value.value: A perimedullary zone (PO:0025058) that is part of a tuber pith (PO:0025052).
A tuber perimedullary zone that is part of an aerial tuber pith.
A tuber perimedullary zone that is part of a subterranean tuber pith.
A perimedullary zone (PO:0025058) that is part of a shoot axis pith (PO:0005041).

definition.value: Can occur in a stem or branch.

value.value: A perimedullary zone that is part of a root pith.
A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) that is elongated and sub-cylindrical to cylindrical and supports another cardinal organ part.

definition.value: Some stalks may be ridged or grooved.

value.value: A portion of storage parenchyma that is part of a seed.

label.value: shoot axis tuber axillary bud meristem

value.value: An axillary bud meristem (PO:0000232) that is part of a shoot axis tuber (PO:0004543).

definition.value: As the bud grows, the meristem switches from being an axillary meristem to being a shoot apical meristem.

value.value: A tuber axillary bud meristem that is part of an aerial tuber.
A tuber axillary bud meristem that is part of a subterranean tuber.
A terminal bud that develops into a reproductive structure.
An axillary bud (PO:0004709) that develops into an reproductive shoot system (PO:0025082).
A shoot axis (PO:00025029) that develops from an axillary bud meristem (PO:0000232) or from equal divisions of a meristematic apical cell (PO:0030007).

definition.value: In vascular plants, branches arise from an axillary bud meristem (PO:0000232) and from divisions of the meristematic apical cell (PO:0030007) in non-vascular plants.

value.value: A megagametophyte (PO:0025279) that is located in a plant ovary ovule (PO:0025490).

definition.value: Produces an embryo sac egg cell (PO:0025123).

value.value: A leaf (PO:0025034) in a non-vascular plant.

definition.value: Non-vascular leaves occur in the gametophyte development stage (PO:0028003) of Bryophytes, plants such as moss and liverwort.

value.value: An axillary reproductive bud that develops into a strobilus.
A terminal reproductive bud that develops into a strobilus.

A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) at the interface between two plant structures, one of which is in a gametophyte development stage (PO:0028003) and one of which is in a sporophyte development stage (PO:0028002), and that has as parts transfer cells (PO:0000078).

definition.value: The transfer cells aid in nutrient transport. Examples include ovary placenta (PO:0020001) and fruit placenta (PO:0004535).

value.value: An axillary shoot that develops from an aerial tuber axillary bud.
A shoot axis internode (PO:0005005) that is part of a branch (PO:0025073).
An axillary shoot that develops from a subterranean tuber axillary bud.

definition.value: See also subterranean tuber axillary bud (PO:0025042).

value.value: A shoot system (PO:0009006) in the sporophytic phase that has as part at least one sporangium (PO:0025094).
A reproductive shoot system (PO:0025082) consisting of a number of sporophylls (PO:0009026) or plant ovule (PO:0020003)-bearing modified leaves (PO:0025034) grouped terminally on a stem (PO:0009047).

definition.value: May be simple or compound. Found in lycophytes such as Selaginella and Lycopodium, sphenophytes such as Equisetum, gymnosperms such as cycad, conifers, gnetophytes and the pollen producing structures of Gingko. The term cone is often used for strobili that are woody. Flowers are sometimes considered bisexual strobili. Some flowering plants such as Alnus have inflorescences called catkins that resemble strobili, but are not.

value.value: A bud that develops into a reproductive shoot system.
A bud that develops into a strobilus.
A gynoecium in the early stages of development, characterized as a ridge on the abaxial surface of the floral meristem that develops from a gynoecium primordium.

definition.value: Common in monocots, including species of Poaceae such as Zea mays. If you are annotating to this structure for Zea mays or other grasses, please also add an annotation to the corresponding floret type. Choose the most specific term possible from: spikelet floret (PO:0009082), ear floret (PO:0006354), lower floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear (PO:0006353), lower floret of sessile spikelet of ear (PO:0006351), upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear (PO:0006350), upper floret of sessile spikelet of ear (PO:0006352). In Zea mays, development of the gynoecium ridge of the upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear occurs via continued overgrowth of the shoot apex (which becomes the ovule primordium) by a ring of gynoecial tissue, leading to the formation of a stylar canal that is detected as a slight protuberance on the mature ovary. Early development of the gynoecium ridge of the lower floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear is very similar to that of the upper floret of the pedicellate spikelet of ear, except the development does not proceed beyond the early ridge stage.

value.value: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is part of a plant structure and consists of a narrow band of cells that undergoes dehiscence upon maturation of the structure.
A dehiscence zone (PO:0025092) that is part of a spore capsule.

definition.value: Found in bryophytes. The capsule annulus is located at the base of an operculum. Upon capsule maturation, cell separation in the annulus allows the operculum to separate from the capsule, aiding in spore dispersal.

value.value: A plant organ (PO:0009008) in which plant spores (PO:0025017) are produced.

definition.value: In bryophytes, particularly in mosses, a sporangium is referred to as a capsule. In seed plants, a sporangium is located in a sporophyll. In pteridophytes, a sporangium is located on the surface of a sporophyll or fertile leaf or borne on a sporangiophore. May be unicellular in some algae.

value.value: A portion of parenchyma tissue (PO:0005421) that is part of a root (PO:0009005).
